Computoser - rule-based , probability -driven algorithmic music  composition   Bozhidar Bozhanov   Independent researcher    bozhidar.bozhanov@gmail.com     Abstract   This paper presents the Computoser hybrid  probability/rule based algorithm for music composition  (http://computoser.com ) and provides a reference  implementation .

5 Algorithm  overvie w  The reference implementation can be seen at:  https://github.com/glamdring/computoser   The algorithm is a sequential one, where multiple  musical elements are selected while progressing.
The list of â€œtop tracksâ€ indicates that at least a  sample of pieces is considered of high musical quality   (http://computoser.com/toptracks ).

A survey with 44 respondents  (http://form.jotformeu.com/form/42482375120348 ) was  conducted and 41% of the respondents se lected â€œartificial  soundâ€ as a primary reason for not liking Computoser  pieces.
